<NOTE>$adv00</NOTE>
<NOTE>For Release in Year-End Editions</NOTE>
<HEAD>Politics, Tragedy, Triumph: 1988 As It Unfolded</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS Dec. 7 entry to reflect downward revision in official
death toll from earthquake; SUBS Dec. 21 entry to update with bomb
blamed for Pan Am crash and revised death toll. Last update moved
Dec. 22, under same b0962 number.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a chronology of the major events of <DATE>1988</DATE>:
   
   JAN. 2 _ <LOCATION>U.S.</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Canada</LOCATION> sign landmark free-trade agreement.
   JAN. 7 _ Record snowfall in the South, record cold across <LOCATION>U.S.</LOCATION>
   <DATE>JAN. 28</DATE> _ Face-to-face negotiations begin between Contras and
Sandinistas. Polygamist 13-day siege ends in <LOCATION>Utah</LOCATION>.
   JAN. 30 _ <LOCATION>Washington</LOCATION> Redskins defeat Denver Broncos 42-10 in
Super Bowl.
   FEB. 3 _ <ORGANIZATION>Contra</ORGANIZATION> aid voted down by <ORGANIZATION>House</ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON>Anthony Kennedy</PERSON>
confirmed as <ORGANIZATION>Supreme Court</ORGANIZATION> justice.
   FEB. 8 _ <PERSON>Dole</PERSON> and <PERSON>Gephardt</PERSON> win <LOCATION>Iowa</LOCATION> caucuses.
   <DATE>FEB. 13</DATE> _ Winter Olympics open in <LOCATION>Calgary</LOCATION>.
   <DATE>FEB. 16</DATE> _ <PERSON>Bush</PERSON> and <PERSON>Dukakis</PERSON> win <LOCATION>New Hampshire</LOCATION> primary.
   <DATE>FEB. 17</DATE> _ Marine Lt. Col. <PERSON>Richard Higgins</PERSON> kidnapped in <LOCATION>Lebanon</LOCATION>.
   FEB. 21 _ <PERSON>Jimmy Swaggart</PERSON> steps down from pulpit in sex scandal.
   <DATE>FEB. 23</DATE> _ Nationalist protests begin in <LOCATION>Soviet Armenia</LOCATION>.
   FEB. 25 _ <LOCATION>Panama</LOCATION>'s President <PERSON>Delvalle</PERSON> fails in attempt to fire
armed forces chief <PERSON>Noriega</PERSON>, indicted on drug charges in <LOCATION>U.S.</LOCATION>
   MARCH 8 _ Super <DATE>Tuesday</DATE>: <PERSON>Bush</PERSON> wins 16 of 17 contests, Democratic
results split.
   MARCH 16 _ <PERSON>Poindexter</PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION>North</ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON>Secord</PERSON>, <PERSON>Hakim</PERSON> indicted on
conspiracy charges in Iran-Contra affair.
   MARCH 23 _ Sandinistas, Contras sign cease-fire agreement.
   <DATE>MARCH 29</DATE> _ <PERSON>Dole</PERSON> drops out of presidential race.
   APRIL 4 _ <ORGANIZATION>Arizona Senate</ORGANIZATION> convicts, removes Gov. <PERSON>Mecham</PERSON>.
   APRIL 16 _ <PERSON>Khalil al-Wazir</PERSON>, senior <ORGANIZATION>PLO</ORGANIZATION> commander, assassinated in
<LOCATION>Tunisia</LOCATION>.
   APRIL 20 _ Two-week Kuwaiti hijacking ends in <LOCATION>Algiers</LOCATION>.
   APRIL 26 _ <PERSON>Bush</PERSON> clinches Republican nomination with win in
<LOCATION>Pennsylvania</LOCATION>. In South Korean election, government party loses
legislative majority to opposition groups.
   MAY 3 _ Three French hostages released in <LOCATION>Lebanon</LOCATION>.
   MAY 4 _ Deadline for illegal aliens in <LOCATION>U.S.</LOCATION> to apply for amnesty.
   MAY 8 _ Mitterrand re-elected in <LOCATION>France</LOCATION>.
   MAY 15 _ Soviets begin Afghan troop withdrawal. Kentucky school
bus collision kills 27.
   MAY 19 _ Disturbed woman shoots one child dead, wounds five and
one adult at <LOCATION>Winnetka</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Ill.</LOCATION>, elementary school.
   MAY 29 _ Reagan-Gorbachev summit begins in <LOCATION>Moscow</LOCATION>.
   JUNE 7 _ <PERSON>Dukakis</PERSON> clinches Democratic nomination with victories in
four primaries.
   JUNE 13 _ ``Cigarette lawsuit'' in <LOCATION>New Jersey</LOCATION> decided in favor of
plantiff.
   <DATE>JUNE 28</DATE> _ Opening day of special Soviet Communist Party
conference that adopts sweeping reforms of Soviet system.
   JULY 3 _ <ORGANIZATION>U.S. Navy</ORGANIZATION> cruiser <LOCATION>Vincennes</LOCATION> shoots down <LOCATION>Iran</LOCATION> Air
jetliner over <LOCATION>Persian Gulf</LOCATION>, killing all 290 aboard.
   JULY 6 _ <ORGANIZATION>Piper Alpha</ORGANIZATION> oil platform explodes in <LOCATION>North Sea</LOCATION>, killing
167.
   JULY 11 _ Terrorist attack on Greek cruise ship kills nine,
wounds 98.
   <DATE>JULY 13</DATE> _ Principles of <LOCATION>Angola</LOCATION> settlement reached in <LOCATION>New York</LOCATION>
talks.
   JULY 20 _ <PERSON>Dukakis</PERSON> nominated for president by Democrats.
   <DATE>JULY 31</DATE> _ <PERSON>Hussein</PERSON> resigns <PERSON>Jordan</PERSON>'s claim to <LOCATION>West Bank</LOCATION>.
   AUG. 8 _ <ORGANIZATION>Perez de Cueller</ORGANIZATION> announces Iran-Iraq cease-fire.
   AUG. 17 _ <PERSON>Bush</PERSON> nominated for president by Republicans. President
<PERSON>Zia</PERSON> of <LOCATION>Pakistan</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>U.S.</LOCATION> Ambassador <PERSON>Raphel</PERSON> killed in plane crash.
   <DATE>AUG. 27</DATE> _ Heavy flooding in <LOCATION>Bangladesh</LOCATION>; at least 1,000 perish.
   <DATE>AUG. 28</DATE> _ Italian precision-flying unit crashes into air show
crowd in <LOCATION>West Germany</LOCATION>, killing 70.
   AUG. 31 _ Thirteen die in <ORGANIZATION>Delta</ORGANIZATION> crash at <LOCATION>Dallas-Forth Worth
Airport</LOCATION>.
   SEPT. 8 _ Firestorm around Old Faithful in continuing <DATE>summer</DATE> of
fire in <ORGANIZATION>Yellowstone National Park</ORGANIZATION> and elsewhere in <LOCATION>West</LOCATION>.
   SEPT. <DATE>12-16</DATE> _ Hurricane Gilbert strikes <LOCATION>Jamaica</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Cayman Islands</LOCATION>,
<LOCATION>Mexico</LOCATION>.
   SEPT. 12 _ West German hostage <PERSON>Rudolf Cordes</PERSON> freed in <LOCATION>Beirut</LOCATION>.
   <DATE>SEPT. 17</DATE> _ Summer Olympics open in <LOCATION>Seoul</LOCATION>.
   <DATE>SEPT. 29</DATE> <ORGANIZATION>_ Shuttle Discovery</ORGANIZATION> launched, resuming <LOCATION>U.S.</LOCATION> manned space
program.
   OCT. 1 _ In major shakeup, <PERSON>Gorbachev</PERSON> becomes Soviet president,
<PERSON>Gromyko</PERSON> retires.
   OCT. 3 _ <LOCATION>Beirut</LOCATION> hostage Mithileshwar Singh, <LOCATION>U.S.</LOCATION> resident, freed.
   OCT. 5 _ President <PERSON>Pinochet</PERSON> loses Chilean referendum.
   OCT. <DATE>19-25</DATE> _ Hurricane Joan kills 184 in <LOCATION>Central America</LOCATION>.
   <DATE>OCT. 20</DATE> _ Dodgers defeat <LOCATION>Oakland</LOCATION> A's to win World Series.
   OCT. 21 _ Deposed Philippine President <PERSON>Ferdinand Marcos</PERSON> and wife,
<LOCATION>Imelda</LOCATION>, indicted on racketeering charges in <LOCATION>New York</LOCATION>.
   <DATE>OCT. 26</DATE> _ Trapped whales in Alaskan Arctic freed in combined
U.S.-Soviet effort.
   NOV. 1 _ <LOCATION>Israel</LOCATION> election, Likud gains slightly.
   NOV. 3 _ Computer virus strikes nationwide research network.
   NOV. 6 _ Soviet dissident <PERSON>Andrei Sakharov</PERSON> arrives in <LOCATION>U.S.</LOCATION> for
visit.
   NOV. 8 _ Bush-Quayle elected.
   <DATE>NOV. 15</DATE> _ <ORGANIZATION>Palestine National Council</ORGANIZATION> proclaims independent
Palestinian homeland. Soviet space shuttle Buran makes first flight,
unmanned.
   <DATE>NOV. 16</DATE> _ In <LOCATION>Soviet Union</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Estonia</LOCATION> declares ``sovereignty.''
   NOV. 21 _ Conservatives win Canadian election.
   DEC. 1 _ Supreme Soviet, national parliament, adopts government
reforms.
   DEC. 2 _ Space shuttle Atlantis launched on four-day mission;
<PERSON>Benazir Bhutto</PERSON> becomes <LOCATION>Pakistan</LOCATION> prime minister.
   DEC. 5 _ <ORGANIZATION>PTL</ORGANIZATION> founder <PERSON>Jim Bakker</PERSON> indicted on fraud charges.
   DEC. 7 _ <PERSON>Gorbachev</PERSON>, at <ORGANIZATION>United Nations</ORGANIZATION>, announces troop
reductions. Devastating earthquake in <LOCATION>Soviet Armenia</LOCATION>; initial
estimates of up to 55,000 killed but government later says under
25,000 confirmed dead.
   DEC. 8 _ <ORGANIZATION>Air Force</ORGANIZATION> jet carrying ammunition crashes into
residential area of <LOCATION>Remscheid</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>West Germany</LOCATION>, killing 5. Palestinians
in <LOCATION>Israel</LOCATION>'s occupied territories mark one year since beginning of
intefadeh.
   DEC. 11 _ Soviet quake relief plane crashes, killing 79; Mexican
market explosion kills 68.
   DEC 12. _ <LOCATION>London</LOCATION> triple train crash kills 33; Yugoslav quake
relief plane crashes, killing 7.
   <DATE>DEC. 13</DATE> _ Yasser Arafat speaks to <ORGANIZATION>United Nations</ORGANIZATION> at session in
<LOCATION>Geneva</LOCATION>; <ORGANIZATION>PTL</ORGANIZATION> assets sold for <MONEY>$65 million</MONEY>.
   DEC. 14 _ <LOCATION>U.S.</LOCATION> announces it will open dialogue with <ORGANIZATION>PLO</ORGANIZATION> after
Arafat says he will accept <LOCATION>Israel</LOCATION>.
   <DATE>DEC. 16</DATE> _ <LOCATION>U.S.</LOCATION> holds first direct talks with <ORGANIZATION>PLO</ORGANIZATION>; political
extremist <PERSON>Lyndon LaRouche</PERSON> convicted of tax and mail fraud conspiracy.
   <DATE>DEC. 21</DATE> _ <ORGANIZATION>Pan Am Boeing</ORGANIZATION> 747 crashes in <LOCATION>Scotland</LOCATION>, killing at least
270 aboard and on the ground; terrorist bomb later blamed. <LOCATION>Israel</LOCATION>'s
right-wing Likud bloc and center-left <ORGANIZATION>Labor Party</ORGANIZATION> decide to form a
new national unity government. Two Soviet cosmonauts end history's
longest space flight _ a year in orbit.
   DEC. 22 _ <LOCATION>South Africa</LOCATION>, <LOCATION>Cuba</LOCATION> and <LOCATION>Angola</LOCATION> sign accords granting
independence to <LOCATION>Namibia</LOCATION>, a South African colony, and pledging to
withdraw 50,000 Cuban troops from <LOCATION>Angola</LOCATION>.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End Adv for Year-End Editions</NOTE>
